name: List
description: Contains methods for the List collection type.

add(object).name: add
add(object).description: Adds an element to the end of the list.

add(integer,object).name: add
add(integer,object).signature: public Void add(Integer index, Object listElement)
add(integer,object).overrideSignature: public override Void add(Integer index, Object listElement)
add(integer,object).description: Inserts an element into the list at the specified index position.

addall(list).name: addAll
addall(list).description: Adds all of the elements in the specified list to the list that calls the method. Both lists must be of the same type.

addall(set).name: addAll
addall(set).description: Add all of the elements in specified set to the  list that calls the method. The set and the list must be of the same type.

clear().name: clear
clear().description: Removes all elements from a list, consequently setting the  list's length to zero.

clone().name: clone
clone().description: Makes a duplicate copy of a list.

contains(object).name: contains
contains(object).description: Returns true if the list contains the specified element.

deepclone(boolean,boolean,boolean).name: deepClone
deepclone(boolean,boolean,boolean).signature: public List<Object> deepClone(Boolean preserveId, Boolean preserveReadonlyTimestamps, Boolean preserveAutonumber)
deepclone(boolean,boolean,boolean).overrideSignature: public override List<Object> deepClone(Boolean preserveId, Boolean preserveReadonlyTimestamps, Boolean preserveAutonumber)
deepclone(boolean,boolean,boolean).description: Makes a duplicate copy of a list of sObject records, including the sObject records themselves.

preserveautonumber.name: preserveAutonumber
preserveautonumber.description: The optional preserveId argument determines whether the IDs of the original objects are preserved or cleared in the duplicates. If set to true, the IDs are copied to the cloned objects. The default is false, that is, the IDs are cleared. The optional preserveReadonlyTimestamps argument determines whether the read-only timestamp and user ID fields are preserved or cleared in the duplicates. If set to true, the read-only fields CreatedById, CreatedDate, LastModifiedById, and LastModifiedDate are copied to the cloned objects. The default is false, that is, the values are cleared. The optional preserveAutonumber argument determines whether the autonumber fields of the original objects are preserved or cleared in the duplicates. If set to true, auto number fields are copied to the cloned objects. The default is false, that is, auto number fields are cleared.

equals(list).name: equals
equals(list).description: Compares this list with the specified list and returns true if both lists are equal; otherwise, returns false.

list2.name: list2
list2.description: The list to compare this list with.

get(integer).name: get
get(integer).description: Returns the list element stored at the specified index.

getsobjecttype().name: getSObjectType
getsobjecttype().description: Returns the token of the sObject type that makes up a list of sObjects.

hashcode().name: hashCode
hashcode().description: Returns the hashcode corresponding to this list and its contents.

indexof(object).name: indexOf
indexof(object).description: Returns the index of the first occurrence of the specified element in this list. If this list does not contain the element, returns -1.

isempty().name: isEmpty
isempty().description: Returns true if the list has zero elements.

iterator().name: iterator
iterator().description: Returns an instance of an iterator for this list.

remove(integer).name: remove
remove(integer).description: Removes the list element stored at the specified index, returning the element that was removed.

set(integer,object).name: set
set(integer,object).signature: public Void set(Integer index, Object listElement)
set(integer,object).overrideSignature: public override Void set(Integer index, Object listElement)
set(integer,object).description: Sets the specified value for the element at the given index.

listelement.name: listElement
listelement.description: The index of the list element to set. The value of the list element to set.

size().name: size
size().description: Returns the number of elements in the list.

sort().name: sort
sort().description: Sorts the items in the list in ascending order.

list&lt;t&gt;().name: List<T>
list&lt;t&gt;().description: Creates a new instance of the List class. A list can hold elements of any data type T.

list&lt;t&gt;(list<t>).name: List<T>
list&lt;t&gt;(list<t>).description: Creates a new instance of the List class by copying the elements from the specified list. T is the data type of the elements in both lists and can be any data type.

listtocopy.name: listToCopy
listtocopy.description: The list containing the elements to initialize this list from. T is the data type of the list elements.

list&lt;t&gt;(set<t>).name: List<T>
list&lt;t&gt;(set<t>).description: Creates a new instance of the List class by copying the elements from the specified set. T is the data type of the elements in the set and list and can be any data type.

settocopy.name: setToCopy
settocopy.description: The set containing the elements to initialize this list with. T is the data type of the set elements.
